{
 "response": "# Perspective Audit \u2014 Multi-Column Pricing Comparison Table\n\n## Step 1 \u2014 Escalated perspectives confirmed\n\nFrom the a11y-critic hand-off:\n\n- **Environmental Contrast \u2014 HIGH** \u2192 deep review (Perspective 2)\n- **Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MEDIUM** \u2192 deep review (Perspective 1)\n- **Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 MEDIUM** \u2192 deep review (Perspective 7)\n\n**Not reviewed (rated LOW upstream):** Vestibular & Motion, Auditory Access, Keyboard & Motor, Screen Reader & Semantic. Their checklists were not run. Where a defect I hit while auditing an escalated perspective clearly *belongs* to one of these, it is recorded in **Escalation Calibration** (Step 6a) as a boundary observation, not smuggled in as a formal finding.\n\n## Step 2 \u2014 Reference sections loaded\n\nLoaded checklists for Perspectives 1, 2, and 7 plus the full ARRM role mapping (all supplied inline in the operating protocol). LOW-perspective sections were not loaded.\n\n## Step 3 \u2014 Artifact understood\n\nSingle React component: a 5-column data table (Features + 4 pricing tiers) with 7 feature rows. Interactive elements: four keyboard-accessible CTA `<button>`s and hover-only feature-label tooltips. Colour, an animated \"Most popular\" badge, and a highlighted \"recommended\" column carry meaning. No forms, no auth, no media, no timeouts.\n\n---\n\n## Step 4 \u2014 Per-perspective checklist walkthroughs\n\n### Perspective 2 \u2014 Environmental Contrast (HIGH)\n\n| # | Checklist item (WCAG) | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Normal text \u2265 4.5:1 (1.4.3) | **FINDING** \u2014 `.tier-price` #767676/12px is **4.20:1** on the `#ebf8ff` recommended column (fails) and 4.54:1 on white (threshold). Intro `<p>` #555 = 7.46:1 PASS. |\n| 2 | Large text \u2265 3:1 (1.4.3) | **FINDING** \u2014 `.amount` #111 = 18.9:1 PASS; `.tier-name` PASS. But `.most-popular-badge` 11px **white on the light end of its gradient = 3.05:1** (this is *small* text, needs 4.5:1) \u2192 fails. |\n| 3 | UI boundaries/states \u2265 3:1 (1.4.11) | PASS \u2014 recommended-column `border-top:3px #2b6cb0` = 5.42:1 vs white. The `#ebf8ff` fill vs white is only ~1.03:1, but state is co-signalled by that border **and** the \"Most popular\" text badge, so the fill is not load-bearing. |\n| 4 | Colour not the sole indicator (1.4.1) | **PASS (rebuts fixture)** \u2014 feature cells use `\u2713` (U+2713) vs `\u2715` (U+2715): shape-distinct, so colour is *not* the sole differentiator. (The real defect \u2014 no AT text \u2014 is a Screen-Reader/1.1.1 issue in a LOW perspective; see Step 6a.) |\n| 5 | No sensory-only instructions (1.3.3) | PASS \u2014 no \"click the green/right one\" style prose. |\n| 6 | Forced-colors / HCM functional | PASS \u2014 colours drop to system colours, at which point `\u2713`/`\u2715` are carried by shape; `:focus-visible` uses `solid` outline (preserved); tooltip/badge inherit system colours. |\n\n**Red-flag scan:** body text below 3:1? No (worst body text 4.20:1). Error state red-only? No error UI. Interactive element invisible in forced-colors? No. \u2192 **No auto-CRITICAL.**\n\n### Perspective 1 \u2014 Magnification & Reflow (MEDIUM)\n\n| # | Checklist item (WCAG) | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Reflow to 320px, no 2-axis scroll (1.4.10) | **PASS (rebuts assumption)** \u2014 a comparison table is the canonical *data-table exception* to 1.4.10, and the author isolated the horizontal scroll to `.pricing-table-wrapper { overflow-x:auto }` so the page itself reflows. Correct pattern. (Visual confirm at 320px recommended.) |\n| 2 | Focus never obscured by sticky/fixed (2.4.11) | PASS \u2014 no `position:sticky`/`fixed` anywhere. |\n| 3 | Text to 200% without truncation (1.4.4) | PASS (source-level) \u2014 no `text-overflow`, no fixed heights, cells wrap; needs visual confirm. |\n| 4 | Adapts to text-spacing overrides (1.4.12) | PASS (source-level) \u2014 no `overflow:hidden` on text boxes, no locked `line-height`/heights; needs bookmarklet confirm. |\n| 5 | Hover/focus content dismissible + hoverable + persistent (1.4.13) | **FINDING** \u2014 tooltip is CSS `:hover`-only: **not dismissible** (no Escape) and **never appears on focus** (`:focus-within` absent). Hoverable prong *is* met (tooltip is a flush DOM descendant), so the magnifier auto-CRITICAL does not fire. Aggravated under magnification by `nowrap` + clipping (see F5). |\n\n**Red-flag scan:** two-axis scroll at 320px? No (table exception, isolated overflow). Text hidden/overlapping at 200%? None in source. Tooltip vanishes before magnifier reaches it? No \u2014 it is hoverable. \u2192 **No auto-CRITICAL.**\n\n### Perspective 7 \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent (MEDIUM)\n\n| Checklist item (WCAG) | Result |\n|---|---|\n| Error messages suggest correction (3.3.3) | N/A \u2014 no forms/errors |\n| Multi-step form doesn't re-ask (3.3.7) | N/A |\n| Auth allows paste/autofill (3.3.8) | N/A |\n| Nav consistent position (3.2.3) | N/A \u2014 single component |\n| Same-function components labelled consistently (3.2.4) | **FINDING (borderline)** \u2014 \"Contact sales\" vs \"Talk to us\" are the same action with different labels |\n| Help mechanism consistent (3.2.6) | N/A |\n| Focus doesn't change context (3.2.1) | PASS \u2014 no `onFocus` side effects |\n| Changing a control doesn't auto-submit (3.2.2) | PASS \u2014 CTAs set local state only |\n| Destructive actions have undo/confirm (3.3.4) | N/A \u2014 no destructive actions |\n| More than one way to reach a page (2.4.5) | N/A \u2014 component |\n| Personal-data inputs have `autocomplete` (1.3.5) | N/A \u2014 no inputs |\n| Timeout warning \u2265 20s (2.2.1) | N/A \u2014 no timeouts |\n| Avoids unexplained jargon/abbreviations | **FINDING (AAA)** \u2014 \"SSO / SAML\", \"SLA\", \"API\", \"OIDC\" unexpanded; definitions locked in the broken hover tooltip |\n| **ND:** predictable layout, no shifts | PASS \u2014 no CLS |\n| **ND:** clear visual hierarchy | PASS \u2014 h1 + intro + headed table |\n| **ND:** no autoplay / continuous motion | **FINDING** \u2014 infinite `shimmer` animation, no `prefers-reduced-motion`, no pause |\n| **ND:** no reliance on memory of prior steps | PASS |\n\n**Red-flag scan:** CAPTCHA/cognitive test? No. Paste blocked? No. Redundant multi-step entry? No. Destructive action without confirm? No. \u2192 **No auto-CRITICAL.**\n\n---\n\n## Step 5 \u2014 Findings\n\n### Finding 1 \u2014 Recommended-column price sub-text fails contrast\n\n**Finding:** The 12px price period sub-text (\"/month\") in `#767676` renders on the recommended column's `#ebf8ff` highlight at **4.20:1**, below the 4.5:1 AA floor for normal text. On the three white columns the same text is 4.54:1 \u2014 nominally passing, but with only 0.04 of headroom (inside rendering/anti-aliasing error).\n**WCAG:** 1.4.3 Contrast (Minimum) (AA)\n**Perspective:** Environmental Contrast\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `.tier-price { font-size:12px; color:#767676 }` composited over `.recommended-header { background:#ebf8ff }` (Pro column) = 4.20:1; over `#fff` = 4.54:1 (WCAG relative-luminance computation).\n**Fix:** Darken the sub-text to ~`#595959` or below so it clears 4.5:1 against **both** `#fff` and `#ebf8ff` (`#595959` \u2248 7:1 on white, \u2248 6.4:1 on `#ebf8ff` \u2014 also clears AAA). Never pick a colour that only passes against the page default when a highlight background exists behind the same text.\n**Calibration note:** The fixture's inline comment claims #767676 \"fails AA for text this visually small and light.\" That is incorrect \u2014 1.4.3 applies a single 4.5:1 floor to all normal-size text; there is no size-scaled ratio. On white, #767676 *passes* (4.54:1). The genuine AA failure is the 4.20:1 caused by the highlight background, which the fixture comment does not identify.\n\n### Finding 2 \u2014 \"Most popular\" badge text fails contrast at the light end of the gradient\n\n**Finding:** The 11px white badge label sits over an animated `#2b6cb0 \u2192 #4299e1` gradient. At the light stop the text-to-background ratio drops to **3.05:1**, below the 4.5:1 AA floor for normal-size text. Because the gradient is animated (`shimmer`), every glyph of the label periodically passes over the low-contrast region.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.3 Contrast (Minimum) (AA)\n**Perspective:** Environmental Contrast\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `.most-popular-badge { color:#fff; background:linear-gradient(90deg,#2b6cb0,#4299e1); font-size:11px }`. White on `#4299e1` = 3.05:1; white on `#2b6cb0` = 5.42:1.\n**Fix:** Cap the light gradient stop so its lightest point keeps \u22654.5:1 against white (e.g. keep both stops \u2264 ~`#2c7fc0`), or place a solid scrim behind the text, or raise size/weight. Validate the **lightest** stop, not the average. (The animation itself is a separate defect \u2014 see F4.)\n\n### Finding 3 \u2014 Feature tooltips are hover-only and not dismissible\n\n**Finding:** Feature-description tooltips are revealed purely by CSS `:hover`. They are **not dismissible** (no Escape) and **never appear on keyboard focus** (`:focus-within`/focus trigger absent). Under magnification an un-dismissible tooltip can occlude the adjacent cells the user is reading.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.13 Content on Hover or Focus (AA)\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** UX Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `.feature-tooltip { display:none }` + `.feature-tooltip-trigger:hover .feature-tooltip { display:block }`; no `:focus-within` rule; trigger is a non-focusable `<span>` with no key handler; `role=\"tooltip\"` present but no `aria-describedby`/`id` association.\n**Fix:** Rebuild as a real disclosure \u2014 make the trigger a `<button>`, reveal on `:hover, :focus-visible` (and JS focus), associate with `aria-describedby`, and support Escape-to-dismiss without moving focus. This one change also resolves the keyboard-reachability and SR-association gaps flagged in Step 6a.\n\n### Finding 4 \u2014 Infinite badge animation with no reduced-motion or pause\n\n**Finding:** The \"Most popular\" badge runs an infinite `shimmer` background animation with no `prefers-reduced-motion` suppression and no pause/stop/hide control. Auto-starting, perpetual motion presented alongside static content is an attention/distraction barrier for many neurodivergent users (and a trigger for vestibular users).\n**WCAG:** 2.2.2 Pause, Stop, Hide (AA)\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent (also Vestibular & Motion \u2014 see Step 6a)\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** UX Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `.most-popular-badge { animation: shimmer 2s linear infinite }` + `@keyframes shimmer {\u2026}`; inline source comment confirms \"No @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)\". Motion is auto-starting, >5s, infinite, and parallel with other content \u2192 squarely within 2.2.2.\n**Fix:** The shimmer is decorative \u2014 prefer removing the loop for a static badge. If any motion is retained, gate it behind `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)` (with a `reduce` fall-back that disables it) and expose a stop control. Fixing this also removes the moving low-contrast region behind the badge text in F2.\n\n### Finding 5 \u2014 Tooltip `nowrap` + clipping context truncates content under magnification\n\n**Finding:** Tooltips use `white-space:nowrap` with `position:absolute; left:0; bottom:100%` inside `.pricing-table-wrapper`, whose `overflow-x:auto` forces `overflow-y` to compute to `auto` (CSS spec), creating a two-axis clipping box. Long strings (\"REST API and webhooks for integrations\") cannot wrap and can be clipped by the wrapper or pushed off-screen at 200\u2013400% zoom.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.10 Reflow (AA); 1.4.4 Resize Text (AA)\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `.feature-tooltip { white-space:nowrap; position:absolute; bottom:100%; left:0 }`; `.pricing-table-wrapper { overflow-x:auto }`.\n**Fix:** Allow wrapping (`white-space:normal` + `max-width`) and render the popover outside the clipping context (portal, or `position:fixed` with collision handling). Confirm the full string is visible at 320px and 400%.\n\n### Finding 6 \u2014 Inconsistent labels for the same CTA action\n\n**Finding:** The two sales-contact CTAs use different labels for the same underlying action \u2014 \"Contact sales\" (Business) vs \"Talk to us\" (Enterprise). Same function, inconsistent identification, which adds decision friction for users who rely on stable labelling. *Borderline: arguably intentional per-tier tone; low real-world impact.*\n**WCAG:** 3.2.4 Consistent Identification (AA)\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `TIERS[].cta`: Business = \"Contact sales\", Enterprise = \"Talk to us\".\n**Fix:** If both routes reach sales contact, use one consistent label (\"Contact sales\"). If the destinations genuinely differ, differentiate on outcome rather than tone.\n\n### Finding 7 \u2014 Unexpanded abbreviations, definitions locked behind the broken tooltip\n\n**Finding:** Visible feature labels use unexpanded jargon (\"SSO / SAML\", \"SLA guarantee\", \"API access\"; tooltip text adds \"OIDC\", \"SAML 2.0\"). Expansions exist only inside the hover-only tooltip (F3), so in practice they are unavailable to keyboard, touch, and many other users.\n**WCAG:** 3.1.4 Abbreviations (AAA)\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n**Severity:** ENHANCEMENT\n**Route to:** Content Author\n**Evidence:** `FEATURES[].label` values; `FEATURES[].tooltip` definitions gated behind the hover-only tooltip.\n**Fix:** Provide always-visible expansions on first use or an accessible glossary. At minimum, fixing F3 makes the existing definitions reachable. (AAA \u2014 reported, not escalated.)\n\n---\n\n### Contract-compatible blocks (new MAJOR findings)\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: env-contrast-recommended-price-subtext\nfingerprint: c0a5e7b31f42\nsource: perspective-audit Environmental Contrast checklist (item 1)\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 1.4.3 Contrast (Minimum)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 AA 1.4.3 \u2014 in scope\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: environmental_contrast=HIGH\nevidence: .tier-price #767676/12px over .recommended-header #ebf8ff = 4.20:1 (over #fff = 4.54:1)\nreproduction_steps: source review + relative-luminance computation; confirm with DevTools contrast picker on the Pro column\nexpected_behavior: normal-size text \u2265 4.5:1 against its actual background in every column\nactual_behavior: 4.20:1 on the highlighted column (fail); 4.54:1 on white (no headroom)\ntrend: new\n```\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: env-contrast-badge-gradient-text\nfingerprint: b2d9f3a10c88\nsource: perspective-audit Environmental Contrast checklist (item 2)\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 1.4.3 Contrast (Minimum)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 AA 1.4.3 \u2014 in scope\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: environmental_contrast=HIGH\nevidence: .most-popular-badge #fff/11px on linear-gradient(#2b6cb0,#4299e1); white-on-#4299e1 = 3.05:1\nreproduction_steps: sample the lightest gradient stop under the label; contrast-check white against it\nexpected_behavior: 11px label \u2265 4.5:1 across the full animated gradient\nactual_behavior: 3.05:1 at the light stop; animation sweeps it under every glyph\ntrend: new\n```\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: magnification-tooltip-hover-only-nondismissible\nfingerprint: 7e1f4a9d2b60\nsource: perspective-audit Magnification & Reflow checklist (item 5)\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 1.4.13 Content on Hover or Focus\nsection_508_fpc_context: 1.4.13 is WCAG 2.1 \u2014 beyond Revised 508's WCAG 2.0 baseline; treat as WCAG 2.2 AA obligation\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: magnification_reflow=MEDIUM\nevidence: .feature-tooltip-trigger:hover .feature-tooltip{display:block}; no :focus-within; non-focusable <span> trigger\nreproduction_steps: keyboard-tab to a feature label (cannot); hover then press Escape (does not dismiss)\nexpected_behavior: content on hover/focus is dismissible (Escape), hoverable, and available on focus\nactual_behavior: appears on hover only; not dismissible; unavailable on focus\ntrend: new\n```\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: cognitive-badge-motion-no-reduced-motion\nfingerprint: 3c8b0f5e9a17\nsource: perspective-audit Cognitive & Neurodivergent checklist (ND: no autoplay/continuous motion)\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 2.2.2 Pause, Stop, Hide\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 AA 2.2.2 \u2014 in scope\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: cognitive_neurodivergent=MEDIUM; vestibular_motion=LOW(recommend MEDIUM)\nevidence: .most-popular-badge{animation:shimmer 2s linear infinite}; no prefers-reduced-motion; no pause control\nreproduction_steps: load with prefers-reduced-motion:reduce \u2014 animation still runs\nexpected_behavior: non-essential motion suppressed under reduced-motion, or a pause/stop/hide control provided\nactual_behavior: infinite shimmer regardless of user motion preference; no stop control\ntrend: new\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 6a \u2014 Escalation calibration (boundary observations, no LOW checklist run)\n\nAuditing the three escalated perspectives surfaced defects whose natural WCAG home is a perspective the critic rated **LOW**. I did **not** run those checklists. But the escalation set looks mis-calibrated, and one omission is the single most severe issue in the component \u2014 recording here per \"name it when you see it\":\n\n1. **Screen Reader & Semantic (rated LOW) \u2192 recommend re-escalate to HIGH; likely CRITICAL.** In `FeatureCell`, the availability glyph is `<span aria-hidden=\"true\">{value ? '\u2713' : '\u2715'}</span>` with **no visually-hidden text equivalent**. Screen-reader users hear nothing for any tier/feature intersection \u2014 the entire comparison payload (who gets API, SSO, SLA, priority support) is silent. **WCAG 1.1.1 / 4.1.2.** This would independently warrant **BLOCK**. Note the interplay with Environmental Contrast item 4: the `\u2713`/`\u2715` shapes *do* differentiate the states for sighted and colour-blind users (so 1.4.1 colour-alone is met) \u2014 the barrier is missing AT text, not colour, which is precisely why it belongs to Screen Reader and not Contrast.\n\n2. **Keyboard & Motor (rated LOW) \u2192 recommend re-escalate to MEDIUM.** The tooltip trigger is a non-focusable `<span>`; tooltip content is unreachable by keyboard (**2.1.1**). Partially captured in F3.\n\n3. **Vestibular & Motion (rated LOW) \u2192 recommend re-escalate to MEDIUM.** The `shimmer` animation lacks reduced-motion handling and a pause control (**2.2.2**). Captured through the Cognitive lens in F4; the primary owner is still Vestibular & Motion.\n\n## Step 6b \u2014 Calibration notes (planted-comment rebuttals)\n\nTwo inline \"BUG\" comments in the fixture assert WCAG failures that do not hold as written; flagging so downstream fixes target the real defect:\n\n- **\"#767676 fails AA for small text\"** \u2014 false. 1.4.3 has no size-scaled ratio for normal text; on white it is 4.54:1 (passes). The real AA failure (4.20:1) is caused by the `#ebf8ff` highlight background on the Pro column \u2014 see F1.\n- **\"check vs X distinction relies entirely on colour\"** \u2014 false. `\u2713` (U+2713) and `\u2715` (U+2715) are shape-distinct, so **1.4.1 is met**. The real defect is the missing AT text (1.1.1), a Screen-Reader issue \u2014 see Step 6a #1.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** Multi-Column Pricing Comparison Table (React `PricingTable`)\n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Environmental Contrast (HIGH), Magnification & Reflow (MEDIUM), Cognitive & Neurodivergent (MEDIUM)\n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Vestibular & Motion, Auditory Access, Keyboard & Motor, Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 *see Step 6a: Screen Reader, Keyboard, and Motion appear under-escalated.*\n\n### Findings by Severity (in-scope / escalated perspectives)\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 0 |\n| MAJOR | 4 |\n| MINOR | 2 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 1 |\n\n*Out of scope but flagged: 1 likely-CRITICAL Screen-Reader defect (Step 6a #1).*\n\n### Perspectives That Passed\n\nNone fully. Every escalated perspective produced at least one finding. Note, however, that several individual checklist items **passed and rebut planted concerns** \u2014 1.4.10 reflow (data-table exception + isolated overflow), 1.4.1 colour-alone (shapes differentiate), and 1.4.3 on white (4.54:1 passes).\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Visual Design**\n- Recommended-column price sub-text 4.20:1 \u2014 Environmental Contrast \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.4.3\n- Badge label 3.05:1 on gradient light stop \u2014 Environmental Contrast \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.4.3\n- Tooltip `nowrap` + clipping truncation under magnification \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.4.10 / 1.4.4\n\n**UX Design**\n- Tooltip hover-only, not dismissible, not on focus \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.4.13\n- Infinite badge animation, no reduced-motion/pause \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.2.2\n\n**Content Author**\n- Inconsistent CTA labels for same action \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 MINOR \u2014 3.2.4\n- Unexpanded abbreviations, definitions behind broken tooltip \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 ENHANCEMENT \u2014 3.1.4\n\n**Front-End Dev**\n- (Secondary owner on every finding above.) Would be **primary** on the boundary Screen-Reader CRITICAL (missing AT text for feature availability, 1.1.1/4.1.2) if that perspective is re-escalated.\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification\n\n- Visual regression at **320px, 200%, and 400%** to confirm 1.4.10, 1.4.4, and 1.4.12 pass at render time (source shows no clipping/truncation mechanisms, but reflow and spacing cannot be fully confirmed from source). `[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]`\n- Text-spacing bookmarklet run (1.5\u00d7 line-height, 2\u00d7 paragraph, 0.12em letter, 0.16em word) to confirm 1.4.12. `[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]`\n- Confirm whether \"Contact sales\" and \"Talk to us\" route to the same flow (determines whether F6 is a real 3.2.4 inconsistency or intentional differentiation). `[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]`\n\n### Recommended Next Step\n\n**REVISE** for the escalated perspectives \u2014 4 MAJOR findings, no in-scope CRITICAL; address before shipping.\n\n**Caveat (do not ship on REVISE alone):** the audit surfaced a **BLOCK-worthy CRITICAL** in an under-escalated perspective \u2014 feature-availability cells are `aria-hidden` with no text equivalent, leaving screen-reader users with an empty comparison table (Step 6a #1). Re-escalate **Screen Reader & Semantic** to HIGH for a dedicated audit and treat the component as **BLOCK** until that defect is confirmed fixed. Also re-escalate **Keyboard & Motor** and **Vestibular & Motion** to MEDIUM.\n",
